NbmaNbrPermanence.description: This variable displays the status of the entry; 'dynamic' and 'permanent' refer to how the neighbor became known.

NbrAddressLessIndex.description: On an interface having an IP address

NbrEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state or an error has occurred.  Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system

NbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor.

NbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this neighbor is using in its IP source address.  Note that

NbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

NbrOptions.description: A bit mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.  Bit 0

NbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF graceful restart interval

NbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

NbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

NbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAddress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

NbrState.description: The state of the relationship with this neighbor.
